        <p>There are an estimated 3 million stray cats in France. These animals often suffer from hunger, disease, and exposure to the elements. While there are many organizations devoted to helping these cats, they need all the support they can get.
          <br>You can help the stray cats of France by donating to one of the many organizations working to help them, or by volunteering your time. Even something as simple as sharing information about these organizations can make a difference. Every little bit helps when it comes to helping these animals.</p>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1514888286974-6c03e2ca1dba?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=MnwxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1443&q=80" alt="" class="show__photo">
        <h4>Hungry cats</h4>
        <p>There are an estimated 30,000 street cats in France, and many of them are hungry. Fortunately, there are a number of ways you can help feed these hungry felines.
          <br>One way to help is by donating to organizations that provide food for street cats. One such organization is Chat du Quartier, which provides dry food and water to street cats in Paris. You can also volunteer to help feed the cats yourself.
